Show date and time
  - date

Display system's uptime:
  - uptime

Display who is currently logged in to the machine
  - who

Display effective username:
  - whoami

Show kernel info
  - uname -a 

Show manual for ls
  - man ls

Generate random data to fill 5GB of disk usage
  - fallocate -l 5G /home/<username>/big_file

Display free disk space for partitions:
  - df -h

Remove file from system:
  - rm <filename>

Show directory size on disk
  - du -sh /path/to/directory

Logout from current session:
  - exit

Print working directory
  - pwd

Navigate from current directory to the parrent one:
  - cd ..

Create a hidden file:
  - touch .hidden file

See a hiden file
  - ls -la

Copy a file
  - cp <source> <destination>

Move a file
  - mv <source> <destination>

Show content of a file
  - cat <filename>
  - more <filename>
  - less <filename>
  - head <filename>
  - tail <filename>

Commands history
  - history


Connect remotely to a machine
  - ssh username@hostname

Search for applications using package managers:
  - apt search <package_name>

Install an application using package manager:
  - apt install <packages_name>

View the machine hostname
  - hostname

Check network interface ip
  - ifconfig / ip

Clear the terminal screen
  - clear


